WEBVTT

00:16.451 --> 00:19.541
A marriage to Julia would be
very good for me, politically.

00:19.541 --> 00:20.933
<i>She's marrying Agrippa.</i>

00:20.933 --> 00:21.934
<i>But he
won't live forever.</i>

00:21.934 --> 00:23.980
And when she does
become available,

00:23.980 --> 00:25.416
I want you to fix it.

00:25.416 --> 00:29.812
Julia has dishonored
her marriage to Agrippa.

00:31.248 --> 00:35.035
It wasn't Vilbia
Julia was sleeping with.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.340
<i>Does it ever bother you</i>

00:36.340 --> 00:38.864
that he adopted my two sons
and never yours?

00:38.864 --> 00:42.085
<i>Love makes us weak.</i>

00:42.085 --> 00:43.869
I saw Gaius's will.

00:43.869 --> 00:47.525
So, the adopted sons of Agrippa
to inherit everything, hmm?

00:47.525 --> 00:49.745
- Who's the executor?
- Domitius.

00:49.745 --> 00:51.399
<i>It was Domitius
behind the famine,</i>

00:51.399 --> 00:52.530
as you suspected.

00:54.097 --> 00:55.272
You still don't believe
she killed my brother?

00:55.272 --> 00:58.623
Revenge on Livia
is your passion, not mine.

00:58.623 --> 01:00.451
- Is that the letter from Mother?
- Yes.

01:00.451 --> 01:02.279
Don't know why she bothered
putting it in code.

01:02.279 --> 01:04.716
Habit, I suppose.

01:04.716 --> 01:07.415
Go get the priestess Aurelia.

01:07.415 --> 01:10.200
I want a copy
of Agrippa's will, too.

01:10.200 --> 01:13.943
I want you to take Germany...

01:13.943 --> 01:15.423
for Rome.

01:15.423 --> 01:17.903
If he ever sees you
as a threat or a problem,

01:17.903 --> 01:19.122
you'll be dead.

01:19.122 --> 01:20.993
You certainly
won't inherit his power.

01:20.993 --> 01:22.473
This is a fucking
enormous honor!

01:22.473 --> 01:23.822
- No, it isn't.
- Yes, it is.

01:23.822 --> 01:25.737
It's a ten-year suicide note,
is what it is.

01:25.737 --> 01:27.478
I'd be asking yourself
why it's got your name on it.

01:27.478 --> 01:29.306
Something wrong with my head.

01:29.306 --> 01:32.483
<i>Bad Tiberius
lives inside Tiberius.</i>

01:32.483 --> 01:33.789
<i>He always has done.</i>

01:33.789 --> 01:36.661
Tiberius, she's dead.

01:36.661 --> 01:38.228
Mostly, he sleeps but...

01:38.228 --> 01:40.317
- Who wakes him up?
- Mother.

01:40.317 --> 01:43.190
Her poisons.

01:43.190 --> 01:45.540
Yes, she said you were bound
to need them.

01:57.465 --> 01:59.467
Please, enough fighting.

01:59.467 --> 02:01.469
Stop it. Silence.

02:01.469 --> 02:03.340
Please help, please.
Listen, stop it.

02:03.340 --> 02:04.602
- Agrippa.
- Come on, lads,

02:04.602 --> 02:06.038
don't piss your mother off.

02:09.825 --> 02:11.305
Agrippa.

02:11.305 --> 02:12.436
All right,
that's enough.

02:12.436 --> 02:14.003
Stop the bloody carriage!

02:14.003 --> 02:16.310
- Enough of this now!
- I said stop!

02:16.310 --> 02:17.180
Agrippa,
they're fighting again.

02:17.180 --> 02:18.964
Lads, lads, oi!

02:18.964 --> 02:21.228
- Agrippina, enough.
- You were told!

02:21.228 --> 02:22.664
Gaius, you're not
sitting together anymore.

02:22.664 --> 02:24.013
- Agrippa.
- Julilla, get her back.

02:24.013 --> 02:25.014
Agrippa!

02:25.014 --> 02:26.320
Agrippa.

02:26.320 --> 02:27.625
- I saw that!
- The baby's coming.

02:27.625 --> 02:29.061
It's fucking coming!

02:29.061 --> 02:31.107
Can you not just wait
till we get back to Rome?

02:31.107 --> 02:32.674
- What?
- No? Right. Okay.

02:32.674 --> 02:33.979
Yeah, yeah.

02:33.979 --> 02:36.330
Okay. Kids, form up!

02:36.330 --> 02:38.070
Gaius!

02:38.070 --> 02:39.637
Lucius!

02:39.637 --> 02:40.943
Julilla.

02:40.943 --> 02:42.727
Ooh, it's coming now.

02:46.731 --> 02:48.864
Julilla?

02:52.998 --> 02:56.524
I'm coming to get you!

03:02.486 --> 03:05.489
Hmm.

03:05.489 --> 03:09.058
I wonder where she could be.

03:22.854 --> 03:25.074
Found you! I win!

03:27.381 --> 03:29.252
Come on!

03:29.252 --> 03:32.255
Come on, sit down.

03:36.738 --> 03:39.741
I found you.

03:39.741 --> 03:43.701
Oh! I'm knackered.

03:43.701 --> 03:46.182
Out of shape.

03:50.447 --> 03:52.449
Don't worry about your mum.

03:52.449 --> 03:54.103
She's all right.

03:54.103 --> 03:55.800
Women love a good fuss.

04:01.502 --> 04:03.808
You know, my dad...

04:03.808 --> 04:08.987
...would bring us here hunting
when I was your age.

04:08.987 --> 04:11.120
We'd check the traps and then--

04:11.120 --> 04:13.209
then my brother and I,
we'd run off,

04:13.209 --> 04:16.081
throw rocks at birds.

04:19.955 --> 04:21.086
Oh, it was magic.

04:24.699 --> 04:26.614
You know...

04:29.617 --> 04:32.141
I've fought battles and...

04:32.141 --> 04:35.057
sunk fleets and...

04:35.057 --> 04:37.364
built temples and aqueducts.

04:39.844 --> 04:43.195
I don't think I've ever been
as happy as I was then.

04:53.336 --> 04:55.425
Except maybe now.

05:09.526 --> 05:11.789
Fuck, it's coming,
I can feel it!

05:41.384 --> 05:47.738
Daddy?

05:47.738 --> 05:50.915
Wake up, Daddy.

05:53.614 --> 05:55.746
There you are.

05:55.746 --> 05:57.748
Look, it's a boy.

05:57.748 --> 06:02.013
A big, fat boy.

06:03.406 --> 06:05.930
What? What's the matter?

06:15.418 --> 06:18.552
Agrippa?

06:30.433 --> 06:32.522
Oh, my love.

06:40.138 --> 06:44.099
Thank you.

06:58.418 --> 07:01.246
What?

09:14.554 --> 09:17.426
My friend.

09:17.426 --> 09:19.210
My brother.

09:24.389 --> 09:27.001
Senator.

09:27.001 --> 09:29.394
General.

09:29.394 --> 09:31.266
Architect.

09:32.876 --> 09:35.444
Warrior.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.189
As long as...

09:43.800 --> 09:45.802
As long as...

09:45.802 --> 09:49.110
this city stands...

09:49.110 --> 09:51.242
on these hills...

09:55.029 --> 09:57.205
...men will remember the name...

09:58.598 --> 10:03.080
Marcus Vipsanius Agrippa.

10:04.560 --> 10:08.042
Hey. Hey. It's all right.

10:08.042 --> 10:12.350
You don't need him anymore.
You don't need him anymore.

10:23.057 --> 10:25.537
Augustus.

10:25.537 --> 10:29.106
This is the final will
of Marcus Vipsanius Agrippa,

10:29.106 --> 10:31.587
held in safekeeping
in the Temple of Vesta.

10:33.720 --> 10:36.070
I wonder what's in it.

10:36.070 --> 10:38.638
You shouldn't joke about that.
Forging wills is sacrilege.

10:38.638 --> 10:40.727
Possibly.

10:53.174 --> 10:55.872
It's brilliant, though.

10:55.872 --> 10:58.701
If you control the temple,
you control the future.

10:58.701 --> 11:01.573
I knew he was leaving
everything to Gaius.

11:01.573 --> 11:03.706
Did you really need
any more money?

11:03.706 --> 11:05.577
Money buys people,

11:05.577 --> 11:08.798
and armies,
you can never have enough.

11:08.798 --> 11:10.147
I'll take my old room.

11:10.147 --> 11:12.062
Put the boys
in Tiberius's old room

11:12.062 --> 11:13.716
and the girls in Drusus's.

11:13.716 --> 11:15.587
The baby can sleep
with the nurse.

11:15.587 --> 11:19.026
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

11:19.026 --> 11:22.246
Have a seat,
darling. Hi, you.

11:22.246 --> 11:26.163
So, Julia, back home
with the parents. How's that?

11:27.469 --> 11:29.427
Still, it's only until they
find you a new husband.

11:29.427 --> 11:31.603
Have they told you
who it is yet?

11:31.603 --> 11:34.084
What? After two marriages
and five children?

11:34.084 --> 11:35.390
No. I'm done.

11:35.390 --> 11:37.609
You're only 27.

11:37.609 --> 11:39.568
You can't seriously imagine
you won't get pimped out again?

11:39.568 --> 11:42.092
Oh, that's hardly
the tone, is it?

11:42.092 --> 11:43.790
What tone would you prefer?

11:43.790 --> 11:46.444
Of course you're welcome
to my husband, such as he is,

11:46.444 --> 11:48.925
but sadly there's no chance
of that happening.

11:48.925 --> 11:50.622
Oh, that is
quite enough of that.

11:50.622 --> 11:53.277
In fact, it's much more
likely to be yours, Antonia.

11:55.149 --> 11:57.064
Why? Have you heard something?

11:57.064 --> 11:59.022
Well, I know Domitius
is interested.

11:59.022 --> 12:01.503
Or then there's Drusus.

12:01.503 --> 12:03.592
- What?
- Or Gallus or Varus.

12:03.592 --> 12:05.072
They'd be worth having
in the Senate.

12:05.072 --> 12:06.595
Or even Tiberius,

12:06.595 --> 12:08.945
now that Vipsania's father
can't vote anymore.

12:08.945 --> 12:12.601
How can you be so callous?

12:12.601 --> 12:14.777
- Plenty of practice.
- Oh, honestly, Marcella,

12:14.777 --> 12:16.083
we're barely into
the mourning period.

12:16.083 --> 12:18.085
Do you have to be
such a fucking bore?

12:18.085 --> 12:21.958
No one gave a slave's ass
about my mourning period.

12:21.958 --> 12:24.656
As soon as Marcella's father
turned to ash,

12:24.656 --> 12:27.790
I was panting away
underneath Antonia's.

12:27.790 --> 12:29.836
I got pregnant so fast

12:29.836 --> 12:32.490
that I wasn't actually sure
whose it was.

12:32.490 --> 12:35.145
- Mother.
- That is my point.

12:35.145 --> 12:37.234
After two husbands,
they left you alone.

12:37.234 --> 12:38.583
And you only had four children.

12:38.583 --> 12:41.630
Yes, but I only had relations
with my husband.

12:41.630 --> 12:43.501
Um, Octavia!

12:45.329 --> 12:47.244
Well, it's a bit late
for self-righteous outrage.

12:49.638 --> 12:50.987
Fuck you, Marcella.

12:50.987 --> 12:52.336
You fucking...

12:52.336 --> 12:53.468
Marcella, stop!

12:53.468 --> 12:55.122
Marcella.

12:56.601 --> 12:58.647
Run, Julilla.

12:58.647 --> 12:59.996
Run for your life.

12:59.996 --> 13:01.868
- Never stop and never look back.
- Get off!

13:01.868 --> 13:03.565
- Stop it!
- It's ridiculous.

13:03.565 --> 13:08.004
Fucking Marcella.

13:08.004 --> 13:10.485
She started taunting Julia
about her next marriage.

13:10.485 --> 13:12.182
What next marriage?

13:12.182 --> 13:14.489
Oh, it's the only thing
anyone wants to talk about.

13:14.489 --> 13:18.319
She said it might
even be one of you two.

13:18.319 --> 13:20.625
Mother's with Piso.

13:24.368 --> 13:26.153
Start packing.

13:26.153 --> 13:28.329
Tell nobody.

13:32.072 --> 13:33.987
I loved Agrippa.

13:33.987 --> 13:36.119
As much as I could.

13:36.119 --> 13:41.124
He was... the balance
between Gaius and me.

13:41.124 --> 13:45.563
His death doesn't
really change the succession.

13:45.563 --> 13:48.088
As far as everyone's concerned,

13:48.088 --> 13:50.612
Augustus's adopted sons
are still first in line

13:50.612 --> 13:52.179
to inherit everything.

13:52.179 --> 13:54.485
But the new will you made
will take care of that,

13:54.485 --> 13:56.574
unless he marries Julia off,

13:56.574 --> 14:00.317
and that really
could complicate everything.

14:00.317 --> 14:03.799
Better he doesn't, for everyone.

14:06.019 --> 14:08.108
But he will.

14:08.108 --> 14:11.154
The choice of husband
will be hugely significant,

14:11.154 --> 14:12.895
politically.

14:12.895 --> 14:14.549
I know.

14:14.549 --> 14:16.899
A mark of particular favor

14:16.899 --> 14:19.510
and influence.

14:19.510 --> 14:22.339
Then it has to be Drusus.

14:28.780 --> 14:33.307
Iullus, I'll leave you to it.

14:33.307 --> 14:34.699
No.

14:34.699 --> 14:37.615
No, what?

14:37.615 --> 14:41.881
No, I can't fix
your marriage to Julia.

14:41.881 --> 14:43.099
Not now. Maybe not ever.

14:43.099 --> 14:47.756
You promised me.

14:49.758 --> 14:54.110
I've done everything you asked.

14:54.110 --> 14:55.938
Gaius will let you run
for the Consul next year,

14:55.938 --> 14:57.113
and I will pay for it.

14:57.113 --> 14:58.941
Everyone's a Consul now.

14:58.941 --> 15:00.856
I want Julia.

15:00.856 --> 15:03.859
You want
the daughter of Augustus.

15:03.859 --> 15:06.079
Why shouldn't I?

15:06.079 --> 15:08.603
I'm sorry.

15:23.444 --> 15:24.967
That's the last time
I'll get betrayed

15:24.967 --> 15:28.840
by your fucking family.
- I doubt that.

15:28.840 --> 15:31.452
My father ruled
the world with yours,

15:31.452 --> 15:33.802
but I'm kept outside
like a fucking leper,

15:33.802 --> 15:37.153
waiting for my turn
as a Consul.

15:37.153 --> 15:39.329
I swear to the gods,

15:39.329 --> 15:43.290
I'll bring this whole
fucking thing crashing down.

15:47.381 --> 15:48.991
No, you won't.

15:48.991 --> 15:53.039
Livia, you listen to me.

15:53.039 --> 15:55.998
My whole life, I've always done
what everyone else wants.

15:55.998 --> 15:58.305
I've earned my freedom.

15:58.305 --> 15:59.741
Even a slave
gets that in the end.

15:59.741 --> 16:01.351
What?

16:01.351 --> 16:04.180
I don't want to
get married again.

16:04.180 --> 16:06.878
I want to be left alone.

16:06.878 --> 16:10.012
And as some sort of woman,
I expect you to get that

16:10.012 --> 16:12.145
and get behind me.
- Agreed.

16:12.145 --> 16:14.321
What?

16:14.321 --> 16:16.366
I don't want you
to get married again.

16:16.366 --> 16:18.368
It's messy,

16:18.368 --> 16:20.588
and it complicates
everything, so...

16:23.895 --> 16:26.376
All right then. Fine.

16:26.376 --> 16:27.290
So, you'll fix it?

16:32.513 --> 16:34.602
Drusus.

16:37.387 --> 16:39.563
The women are all talking about
who's next for Julia.

16:39.563 --> 16:41.217
If I can't put it off,

16:41.217 --> 16:44.003
it will have to be you.

16:46.266 --> 16:47.484
Will that bother you?

16:50.879 --> 16:52.402
I love Antonina.

16:52.402 --> 16:55.231
But it's just a marriage.

16:55.231 --> 16:57.755
Nobody takes it personally.

16:57.755 --> 17:00.367
What matters
is getting the Republic back,

17:00.367 --> 17:03.892
and if I have to marry Augustus
to do that, then I will.

17:10.768 --> 17:14.772
Prepare your wife.

17:14.772 --> 17:17.906
Domitius will want Julia, too.

17:17.906 --> 17:21.475
You can leave that to me.

17:26.132 --> 17:28.873
Find my sister, please.

17:32.747 --> 17:35.271
And Scribonia,

17:35.271 --> 17:37.534
Livia.

17:45.847 --> 17:49.546
We'll rely on
these measures...

17:49.546 --> 17:50.460
Domitius.

17:53.985 --> 17:57.554
- Excuse me.
- Yes, of course.

17:57.554 --> 18:00.470
Livia.

18:00.470 --> 18:02.994
Are you looking for me?

18:02.994 --> 18:07.347
I want to ask you
to speak to Augustus today.

18:07.347 --> 18:10.001
Tell him that out of respect
for your wife Antonia,

18:10.001 --> 18:13.788
you can't be considered
as husband for Julia.

18:13.788 --> 18:16.660
And why would I do that?

18:16.660 --> 18:20.577
Because it would make me happy.

18:20.577 --> 18:22.927
Well, I hate to make you sad,

18:22.927 --> 18:24.799
but if Augustus

18:24.799 --> 18:26.757
is looking to marry
his daughter to anyone,

18:26.757 --> 18:29.934
then I would expect
to be considered.

18:29.934 --> 18:32.589
And I certainly
wouldn't turn her down.

18:32.589 --> 18:34.330
Hmm.

18:34.330 --> 18:38.291
Domitius.

18:38.291 --> 18:39.683
Was that all?

18:42.643 --> 18:44.645
You know, I never told Augustus

18:44.645 --> 18:46.603
that you organized
that grain famine...

18:49.040 --> 18:53.219
...with your close friend,
Marcus Cassius Elva.

18:53.219 --> 18:55.656
That's where you got the money
to run for Consul.

18:55.656 --> 18:57.788
That's a lie.

18:57.788 --> 19:02.053
My people found
your agent in Egypt,

19:02.053 --> 19:04.447
Tomi, the one
you used to buy the grain,

19:04.447 --> 19:07.058
which you sold to Rome
for six times the price.

19:07.058 --> 19:10.366
Well, he was tortured
until he told us everything.

19:10.366 --> 19:14.849
So, you know...

19:14.849 --> 19:17.678
That's all.

19:27.035 --> 19:29.516
Are you divorcing me for Julia?

19:32.606 --> 19:35.391
If things work out,

19:35.391 --> 19:37.567
I might have to.

19:37.567 --> 19:39.830
Are we still going
to Germany tomorrow?

19:39.830 --> 19:41.397
Of course.

19:41.397 --> 19:43.182
Nothing will happen
till next year.

19:50.798 --> 19:53.931
Oh, well, that's it, then.

19:58.414 --> 20:00.721
Still...

20:00.721 --> 20:06.117
it was fun
while it lasted.

20:06.117 --> 20:10.034
It'll be me
who has to marry Julia.

20:10.034 --> 20:11.558
What?

20:11.558 --> 20:13.690
Stepfather loves Drusus,

20:13.690 --> 20:16.476
because everybody loves Drusus,

20:16.476 --> 20:18.565
but he's jealous of him,
and I think he fears him, too.

20:21.742 --> 20:25.398
He won't give him
his daughter.

20:25.398 --> 20:29.053
He'll give her to someone who--
who he doesn't fear at all,

20:29.053 --> 20:32.753
someone everyone thinks
is useless.

20:32.753 --> 20:35.059
Yes, you're clearly
the most useless choice.

20:35.059 --> 20:37.497
Deep down,
he'll enjoy giving Julia

20:37.497 --> 20:39.803
to the only person in Rome
who doesn't want her.

20:39.803 --> 20:41.762
Because he's a monster.

20:41.762 --> 20:44.330
Plus...

20:44.330 --> 20:47.463
of course you're
irrelevant now, politically,

20:47.463 --> 20:48.682
after your father's death.

20:48.682 --> 20:51.989
Meaningless.

20:51.989 --> 20:55.341
We can't take the baby with us.

20:55.341 --> 20:58.648
He'll slow us down,
and it won't be safe.

20:58.648 --> 21:01.521
Antonina will look after him.

21:11.313 --> 21:16.057
Are you ready then?

21:16.057 --> 21:21.280
I have been ready all my life.

21:30.201 --> 21:31.246
Domitius.

21:31.246 --> 21:34.728
I was just leaving.

21:36.033 --> 21:38.384
He's not well.

21:38.384 --> 21:40.995
I've told him that he should
stop having these meetings,

21:40.995 --> 21:42.953
that it's too tiring,
but he won't listen.

21:42.953 --> 21:45.260
I'm all right.
It's just a chill.

21:45.260 --> 21:47.001
What did Domitius want?

21:47.001 --> 21:50.613
Oh, Domitius said
that he would prefer

21:50.613 --> 21:54.530
not to be considered
if Julia were to remarry.

21:54.530 --> 21:56.140
But he was very nice about it.
I mean, I thought

21:56.140 --> 21:58.055
he was very respectful.
- Mmm.

21:58.055 --> 22:02.886
Listen, Livia,
now that we're all here,

22:02.886 --> 22:04.975
I have a gift for you.

22:06.237 --> 22:08.327
Julia.

22:10.241 --> 22:11.895
She'll have to marry again.

22:11.895 --> 22:15.856
This time I want it
to be into your family.

22:15.856 --> 22:17.814
So...

22:17.814 --> 22:19.860
she'll marry Tiberius.

22:23.211 --> 22:26.214
Tiberius?

22:26.214 --> 22:30.871
And then maybe we can have
grandchildren together, finally.

22:30.871 --> 22:33.134
Oh, thank you.

22:33.134 --> 22:35.745
Yes, thank you.

22:35.745 --> 22:38.226
Well, I--I'm just grateful

22:38.226 --> 22:40.750
that none of my daughters
have to get divorced,

22:40.750 --> 22:42.404
'cause that's
always a bore, isn't it?

22:42.404 --> 22:43.666
They have to come home,

22:43.666 --> 22:46.277
and they just complain
about everything.

22:46.277 --> 22:48.541
I know I'd normally consult you
over something like this,

22:48.541 --> 22:52.588
but I wanted it
to be a surprise.

22:52.588 --> 22:55.243
